Text.SourceString: Oh, hey! I have to say, you’re not what I expected.
Oh no, I didn’t mean it in a bad way.//I heard from the twins who run the inn that a new farmer moved in.//I just thought…you know…//Never mind.
I’m convinced something’s living in the recycling area next to the community center.

I’m not going to waste time trying to convince you. I know what I saw.//<portrait=normal>Some time ago, as I was walking home, I saw <Italic>something</> running really fast toward the bins.//And get this! I asked around the next day, and <NpcName>Pablo</> said he heard the buzzing noise too.
Let me ask you, <PlayerName>$player</>. How can there be a buzzing noise in a place with no machines?
Who’s talking about me? <Italic>I’m</> not talking about me.

Special.SourceString: It can’t. You must have misheard.

Text.SourceString: The blacksmith’s place is very close to the recycling center. Hmm… It could be.

Special.SourceString: A machine someplace nearby must have made the noise.

Text.SourceString: Bam!//<portrait=normal>Your words, not mine.
I can’t wait for the recycling center to be fixed up.
I can’t wait for the dumpster to rebuild.
I’m convinced that something’s living in the dumpster next to the community center.

I’m not going to waste my time trying to convince you. I know what I saw.//<portrait=normal>Sometimes ago when I was walking home, I saw <Italic>something</> running really fast towards the dumpster.//And, get this! I asked around the next day, and <NpcName>Pablo</> said he heard the buzzing noise too.
When the mayor finally gives approval to put in a community garden, my mom will be ecstatic.
I have a feeling she’ll be gardening there twenty-four seven.
When the mayor finally approves the building of a community garden, my mom will be ecstatic.
I have a feeling she’ll be gardening there 24-7.
When the mayor finally approves the building of a community garden, my mom will be ecstatic.
I have a feeling she’ll be gardening there 24-7.
I like this town. It may not be Pokyo, but it’s home to me.//That’s hard to beat.
Where else can we get a white-sand beach at a lake, huh?
My favorite hiding spot used to be behind the welcome sign.
Oh, not from people!//<portrait=normal>It was my hiding spot when I was playing hide-and-seek.
No, not much has changed… Starlet has looked like this since I was little.//Every corner holds so many memories.
My favorite hiding spot used to be behind the Welcome sign.
Oh, not from people! It was my hiding spot when I was playing hide-and-seek.
Not much has changed here… Starlet has looked like this since I was a little boy. Every corner holds so many memories.
My favorite hiding spot used to be behind the Welcome sign.
Oh, not from people!//<portrait=normal>It was my hiding spot when I was playing hide-and-seek.
To me, durian tastes exactly like it smells.//<portrait=happy>Prickles aside, it’s simply the best part of Spring.
Baking a cake is way more complicated than it looks.//For starters, it requires a lot of ingredients.
I don’t have a lot of spare time to do things like cooking for fun.//It takes a lot to run a dining establishment.
My mom has a reputation as the best baker around.//If you want to learn a few baking tricks, you should get to know her.
I tend to do my errands before noon. Trying to get things out of the way.//That way, I can work in peace.
Something about being at the Tavern makes some people share too much, too soon.//<portrait=sad>Hmm…
Maybe it’s that “mixed punch” <NpcName>Frank’s</> serving.
I don’t have work today. The Tavern is closed.//What’s up?
Yes, we’re open again tomorrow.
We mainly buy supplies from <NpcName>Sam</>.//It’s our way of supporting other local businesses.
I’m turning in early today.
Oh, nothing. I just have an early start tomorrow morning.
We could use more help running the Tavern, but <NpcName>Frank</> is against it.//<portrait=concerned>He thinks it would be throwing money down the drain.
Hard to talk about hiring more help with <NpcName>Frank</>.//He and I don’t see eye to eye.
Ah… Sorry about that.
We do our own grocery shopping and cooking.//<portrait=annoyed>It’s very time consuming, if you ask me.
After working at Fishensips for a while, I think selling drinks is where the money’s at.//<portrait=angry>If it were up to me, the Tavern would cut down on serving food and expand the drink menu.
Besides, serving drinks is much easier than serving food.//It’s less messy, especially with big groups of people.
Do you want to sign up for the live performance?//We only have <NpcName>Theo</> so far. I think he’s all right. People like his energy.
<NpcName>Theo</> gets some quick money, and we get to advertise live music at the Tavern.//<portrait=normal>People are drawn to live music for some reason.
The universe is so big, don’t you think? I think it’s a bit cocky to believe all this is only for us to enjoy.
The more I read about UFOs, legends, and myths, the more I think we’re not alone in this world.
I work today. But only a half-shift.
How are you doing today, <PlayerName>$player</>?
<NpcName>Frank</> doesn’t mind working long hours.//He likes it.
I always say I’ll go to sleep early, but I end up watching TV until way too late.
<NpcName>Frank</> is a good cook. But not much variety, you know?//<portrait=normal>He also has this tendency to substitute ingredients.
Sometimes you don’t really know what you’re getting yourself into.
<NpcName>Frank</> isn’t the oldest in the family.//<portrait=normal>We have an older sister who lives abroad… Four siblings total.
Ah, wrong again. I’m also not the youngest in the family.//Our baby brother works at a start-up in a valley across the ocean.
<NpcName>Frank</> isn’t the oldest in the family.//<portrait=normal>We have an older sister who lives abroad… Four siblings, total.
Ah, wrong again. I’m also not the youngest in the family.//Our baby brother works at a start-up in a valley across the ocean.
I don’t mind doing the shopping.//That way, <NpcName>Frank</> can focus on cooking.
Finding the right balance between working and taking time for yourself is important.//It helps you refocus on your goals.
<NpcName>Alice</> mentioned how weird it is that some flowers bloom at night.//Like, after the sun sets.//Don’t flowers need the sun to bloom?
I guess not. Hmm…
Well… Yeah, <NpcName>Frank</> is a good cook. But not much variety, you know?//<portrait=normal>He also has this tendency to substitute ingredients.
Sometimes you don’t really know what you’re getting yourself into.

Strongest memory?//<portrait=normal>Hard to choose, but pranks might be some of the main ones…//<portrait=happy>Growing up with a lot of siblings means you learn a new prank every day – I can attest to that!
<NpcName>Frank</> was born in Summer, which is probably why he’s always energetic and upbeat…//<portrait=happy>Is that even a thing?
Growing up with three siblings, every day felt like somebody’s birthday at our house.
Why does it feel like it’s somebody’s birthday every day?

One of these days, I’m gonna miss somebody’s birthday…//<portrait=sad>I just know it.//<portrait=concerned>And that somebody will get upset because they remembered mine…//These social norms are just so hard to keep track of.
It’s really not on purpose.//<portrait=sad>It’s just overwhelming to keep up with birthdays sometimes.
Having three siblings taught me there’s no such thing as personal space.
Gah. I miss <NpcName>Eddy</>.
When I was growing up, Mom and Dad assigned each of us a roommate.//<portrait=happy>I was with <NpcName>Frank</>, and my sister was stuck with our youngest brother, <NpcName>Eddy</>.
I hope it won’t rain tomorrow. I need to visit the vineyard to pick up some wine…//<portrait=normal>The Tavern is dangerously low.
I’m not like my kitchen-warrior brother, <NpcName>Frank</>. I’m afraid I can only cook sunny-side up.
Do you think that’s good enough?
Please don’t order the “mixed punch” – it’s mostly <NpcName>Frank’s</> failed experiment. Spare yourself a stomachache.
I grew up eating <NpcName>Frank’s</> experimental food, and that just might be why I’m a picky eater now.
My dad used to say, “To test a marriage, you should either open a restaurant or have a bunch of kids.”
My parents did both, and they survived! I know he was joking, but I think it’s accurate.
Well, what else am I going to do on my day off?
<NpcName>Frank</> and I can’t take the weekend off. That’s when the Tavern is the busiest.
The Tavern could charge a premium for drinks and meals, don’t you think? We use only the best ingredients.
I don’t think we’ll lose customers if we just increase the price by 20 percent. But we’re too afraid to risk it, I guess.
One thing I don’t miss about Pokyo, though, is the constant blaring of car horns.
I lost a lot of sleep because of that, which inevitably affected my mood.
Please don’t order the “mixed punch” – it’s mostly <NpcName>Frank</>’s failed experiment. Spare yourself a stomachache.
I grew up eating <NpcName>Frank</>’s experimental food, and that just might be why I’m a picky eater now.
I’m not like my kitchen-warrior brother, <NpcName>Frank</>. I’m afraid I can only cook sunny-side up.
Do you think that’s good enough?
I’m looking forward to taking my mom to the beach next week.
I had a lot of fun with her this week, walking around town and catching up.
I’m looking forward to taking my mom to the beach next week.
The best memory with my mom?//Ah… Tricky question. I don’t know. I have too many good memories with my mom at the beach. It’s hard to pick just one.
There are so many interesting Spring crops. I don’t understand why <NPCName>Frank</> won’t introduce a seasonal menu to take advantage of them.
Honestly, at this point, I’m just counting down the days until Summer.
If Mom can cook seasonal food, why can’t <NPCName>Frank</>? And why can’t we serve it at the Tavern?//<portrait=normal>Now’s the perfect time for a seasonal menu.
<NPCName>Frank</> and I are getting ready for the Cherry Blossom Festival.//Mom and Dad used to help make the hot pot, but we took over, even before Dad passed away.
The trees in Pokyo never looked this beautiful in Spring.//<portrait=happy>I’m so glad I moved back here right after I graduated.
I’m gathering all the ingredients for the hot pot.//<portrait=happy>Well, other than the ones the townsfolk are bringing, of course.
Finally, it’s Summer!//Have you planted your Summer crops yet?
With the temperature rising, I think I’ll take Mom to Hillside for morning walks… Too much beach isn’t good for her.
Our air conditioner broke the other day. Thankfully, <NPCName>Pablo</> fixed it.//Some of the wiring was moldy, apparently. Good thing it wasn’t anything worse, like rats.

I was thinking maybe we could open a booth at one of the festivals, like the annual beach cleanup. Perfect, right?//We could sell cold drinks, homemade sweets… I don’t know. People swim, they get hungry. Simple logic to me.//But <NPCName>Frank</> won’t even give it a chance. Not enough staff.

<NPCName>Alice</> thinks there’s intelligent life in the sky, but my money is on under the water.//<portrait=normal>Did you know we’ve explored less than 20 percent of the ocean?//<portrait=surprised>There’s gotta be merfolk or something living in the other 80 percent!
I need to tell Mom to wear her hat. She can’t be walking around in this Summer heat without one.//I’m worried she might get light-headed at the lake, and…//I don’t even wanna think about it.
Sometimes <NPCName>Alice</> invites me to go to the forest to look for cryptids, but I’d rather search in the ocean or around the beach.

<PlayerName>$player</>! I saw something swimming in the distance the other day, and it was shimmering. It must have been a merperson! Wait until I tell <NPCName>Alice</> about this.//Or it could’ve been <Italic>another</> seal, like that one time…
The tide can get pretty high in Summer, but so far, it hasn’t ever reached the Tavern.//Thank goodness, right? That sounds expensive to fix.
You know, there’s a folk legend that says the daisy patches in Summer are places where they’ve buried a pure and innocent child who died.
But another story says they’re where the fairies sleep.//I like the fairy story better, honestly.
Such a bummer that Summer is over. But I guess it means I can focus more on the Tavern.
The beach is still pretty fun in Fall, but not as much as it is in Summer.
Our family wasn’t as busy for the Harvest Festival… Yeah, we helped out.//But we pretty much hosted the Cherry Blossom Festival.
I think Fall is the best season for eating roasted mushrooms. It’s the best season for making them too!//They’re sprouting in the wild. You can hunt for them in the forest.
I don’t know why anyone would eat mushrooms raw. Ew.//<portrait=happy>Now roasted, that’s the way to go.
I managed to find tons of mushrooms the other day! Now I just need to roast them all.//Not a big fan of cleaning them, though. It’s a lot of work.//The dirt just doesn’t seem to come off.
Are you ready for the New Year’s Eve Festival? I know I am.//<portrait=happy>Yes, I know this is still the first week of Winter, but you can never prepare too early!

I can’t wait to eat all the good food at the New Year’s Eve Festival.//The Duckorns, <NPCName>Luke’s</> family, usually have it catered by fancy Pokyo restaurants.//They had garlic ice cream a few years ago… It was weird but delicious.
Gotta say I’m not a big fan of the cold, but then again, who is, right?//Wait… Are you?

I have a video camera in my room that I usually leave on during Winter nights to record the sky.//One time, when I was about <NPCName>Archie’s</> age, I stayed up watching TV. It was pretty late, and I saw something flying in the sky – a sleigh.//I know, I know. But I know what I saw, so I’m trying to catch it on video.

If it were warmer, I think I’d spend more time outside, but as it is?//<portrait=normal>I think I’ll just do the paperwork for the Tavern.//Somebody’s gotta do the accounting, and it isn’t gonna be my big bro.
Restocking supplies and doing paperwork is much better than being outside in the cold.
If you have time, try some of our food and drinks. They’re the islanders’ favorites.
They also make great gifts.//It’s an easy way to win people over, you know?
A couple of very well-dressed people came here last year and started taking pictures. But they weren’t acting like tourists, you see.
They mostly kept to themselves, and they each had a little yellow brooch on their jacket. I guess they were Pufferfish employees, surveying the area.
*humming*
We’ll be at the Cherry Blossom Festival on Wednesday. <NPCName>Frank</> will be grilling all day, so we should probably arrive a bit early to get things ready.
They should at least consider having another potluck this Summer.

Oh… Maybe we can have a potluck in Fall and Winter too…//<portrait=normal>When people bring their favorite dish for the community to enjoy, the gathering is more meaningful. It has that big-family feel.
Tomorrow is the first day of Summer.//<portrait=normal>Get ready, <PlayerName>$player</>. It’s going to get really hot.
It’s only the beginning of Spring, but I already can’t wait to spend my Summer soaking up some sun at the beach.
Another exciting thing about Summer is merfolk supposedly come out in the warmer weather…//<portrait=happy>Makes no sense whatsoever.//<portrait=normal>Also, impossible to prove.
Are you excited for your first Summer here, <PlayerName>$player</>?
I’m taking a bit of a break today, just trying to spend time outdoors.
It’s Summer, after all. Right?
You can learn a thing or two from your neighbors.//You might pick up a simple recipe to try out or even learn how to craft items for your farm.
Get to know them, and they might share their knowledge with you.

Hmm… It feels incredibly humid today!//<portrait=annoyed>I hate the sticky feeling in Summer.//<portrait=concerned>The heat is nice sometimes, but when it’s this hot, just being outside can be tiring. Even if I’m doing nothing.
Sorry if I’m complaining too much.//<portrait=sad>I guess it’s just one of those days.
I picked up some coconuts from the beach the other day. They can be a quick hydration solution…//<portrait=surprised>Bah!//<portrait=blushing>That was a mouthful to say.
The wind is getting colder. I think Fall is finally here.
<NPCName>Frank</> needs more help in Fall, so I usually work extra shifts on Sundays.
If I don’t keep an eye on my mom, who will?
My siblings all left the nest already. I’m all she’s got left.
Taking a break from the farm, <PlayerName>$player</>?
I’ve been baking a lot more lately, but nothing’s turned out good… Bummer!
I don’t have a sweet tooth, so I think it’s just the cold weather getting to me. You know, having a bigger appetite and all.
It’s truffle season. I’m keeping an eye out in case I spot one in the wild.
They’re rare, though.
Mom and I used to spend my birthday hunting for truffles and Winter vegetables in the forest. Then at night, she’d cook them up as a side dish for ramen.
We spent way too much money on a new heater for the Tavern.
The old one was fine. But <NPCName>Frank</> thought it was important to get a new heater in case the old one broke in the middle of Winter.
I haven’t complained once about how cold it is this Winter.//Go, me!
The weather is putting people in a good mood.
You must not have a lot of watering to do today, eh?
I hope there isn’t a leak in the community center.
I’m going to check on the library when the rain settles down.
Something warm sounds good right now.
Is it actually darker than usual outside, or am I losing my mind?
The Tavern gets extra muddy when it rains.//<portrait=annoyed>People just don’t bother wiping their feet.
Is it actually darker than usual outside, or am I losing my mind?
The tavern gets extra muddy when it rains.//<portrait=annoyed>People just don’t bother wiping their feet.
Oh, um…be safe out there, <PlayerName>$player</>.//The storm is really bad today.
I don’t know if it’s safe to walk around in this weather.//<portrait=sad>What am I thinking?
Your cheeks are getting red. You need to warm up, <PlayerName>$player</>.
When I was in elementary school, our sister would boil potatoes in the morning to put in our coat pockets.
The potatoes were to keep our hands warm.//Then we would eat them when we got to school.
I walked past your farm on my way to <NpcName>Ben’s</> the other day.//It looked so beautiful covered in snow.
I hope you don’t mind if I stop by your place sometime.
I keep telling Mom to see <NpcName>Yuri</> for her hip pain, but she keeps ignoring it.//<portrait=concerned>She told me it’s just old age.
Even if it’s just normal joint pain, why not get a professional opinion, right?
<NpcName>Alice</> likes to keep warm by staying active, but not me.//I’d rather bundle up in bed.
I walked past your farm on my way to <NpcName>Ben</>’s the other day.//It looked so beautiful covered in snow.
I hope you don’t mind if I stop by your place sometimes.
I walked past your farm on my way to <NpcName>Ben</>’s the other day.//It looked so beautiful covered in snow.
I hope you don’t mind if I stop by your place sometimes.
I can’t bear the thought of moving out and leaving my mom alone.
I know she says she’s fine, but I don’t want to see her all alone in this big building.
I bumped my head trying to clean the cabinet this morning.
It still hurts.

Hmm… It feels incredibly humid today!//<portrait=annoyed>I hate the sticky feeling in the summer.//<portrait=concerned>The heat is nice sometimes, but in this heat, just being outside can be tiring. Even if I’m doing nothing.
I’m sorry if I complain too much.//<portrait=sad>I guess it’s just one of those days.
Good morning, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=normal>You’re out early today. Running errands?
I make a habit of checking the weather channel every morning before heading out.//You know, in case it might rain or something.
I’ll just have a small breakfast here before my doctor’s appointment at noon.
Yeah, I’m okay, thanks for asking. //<portrait=normal>Just going for a checkup.
I think I just caught one of my brother’s cats trying to sneak in here.
I’ll check on the cats later before I go to work.
*mumbling* Oil, two loaves of bread…
No matter how often you sweep the Tavern’s balcony, it’s impossible to keep it clean this time of year.//The leaves are falling constantly.
Your farm is just over the creek, right?
When it’s not raining, I try to come here every Sunday to watch the sunset.
You can watch the sunset every day from your farm, yeah?//<portrait=happy>So lucky!
We live in the middle of town. Ugh…//<portrait=normal>I wish the Tavern was closer to the beach.//I’m pretty sure it would bring us more business, too.
Have you been inside the lighthouse, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Ah, I can’t look down the cliff.
It’s giving me a headache…//My head is pounding.//Nope!
I might grow my hair out after this.
I might stay here a little longer to cool off.
It’s so hot outside.//I’m glad <NpcName>Sam</> has his air conditioner on full blast.
Oh, bees! Why is it so cold in here?!//<portrait=surprised>With the snow and all, you would think <NpcName>Sam</> would turn down the coolers a bit.
*shivers* I’ve got to get my shopping done fast. It’s too cold in here.//I can’t think.
Some people believe humanoid creatures live in the deep forest…//Legend has it they’re imprisoned by an evil spirit and can’t return to their village.
Yeah, I’m not sure!//<portrait=normal>I like reading up on legends and stuff, but I can’t find many books on it. One book referred to them as Giants.//Tiny Giants, to be exact.
The most interesting legends? Hmm… It’s hard to pick.//The crying rock is an interesting one.
Do I believe them? That’s another story… It would be on a case-by-case basis.//<portrait=normal>I don’t believe everything I read…//Most of them are just for fun.
The house is filled with <NpcName>Aaliyah’s</> trophies. Don’t bother looking for mine. Never contributed to the collection.//She’s been collecting rewards like Dokepon cards since we were little!
With all the coconuts around the island free to harvest, I wonder if we should start selling coconut drinks at Fishensips.//It’s a great way to hydrate, and the base cost is dirt cheap.
But the Beach Shack is already selling coconut drinks…hmm. Not sure if it’s the right thing to do.//I should talk to my sister about it, get some advice. <NpcName>Aaliyah</> is good with numbers.
With all the coconuts around the island free to harvest, I wonder if we should start selling coconut drinks at Fishensips.//It’s a great way to hydrate and the base cost is dirt cheap.
But Beach Shack is already selling coconut drinks…hmm…not sure if that’s the right thing to do.//I should talk to my sister about it…get some advice. <NpcName>Aaliyah</> is good with numbers.
I know Winter has just started, but let me get this off my chest.//The moment Summer is here, I pledge to never leave the beach.
I’ll camp there and enjoy every minute of the salty Summer breeze.
It’s kind of bittersweet to see the cats now that Dad has passed away.//<portrait=sad>It brings back a lot of memories.
I’m not sure how old the cats are, Peanut and Butter… But they’ve been around since Dad was alive.
I’ve always been close to my mom. I wish I could have had a bit more time with Dad, but it’s no use mourning now.
Dad had a happy and long life. I don’t think it’s fair for me to ask for more.//After all, a long and happy life is all anyone wants, right?
Guess what I studied back in university?
Do I look artistic to you? That’s a huge compliment. Thank you. But, no, I studied accounting, actually.
How did you know? Did you study accounting too?
No, I studied accounting. I wish I knew more about literature, though.
I run a tavern and move around a lot. What am I supposed to wear, if not a polo shirt?
I don’t want to look unprofessional, but I also don’t want to be uncomfortable.

Growing up, Mom would always tell us red is a lucky color and to wear it on special occasions, like a wedding or New Year’s.//<portrait=happy>But we don’t always follow things like that to a T. <NpcName>Frank</> didn’t wear red at his wedding. No big deal!
Mom’s family is pretty strict about wearing red on New Year’s.//Whenever we celebrated with them, Grandma used to always dress us up in red. No exceptions!
Dad’s side of the family doesn’t have that culture. We didn’t need to wear red with him…or Mom, actually.//She’s kind of modern that way.

Back in my university days, my dorm was right next to a temple, and whenever Mom came to visit me, we’d go there and pray.//<portrait=happy>Mom would make sure we burned enough incense for our ancestors.
I remember smelling like ash for the rest of the day.//<portrait=normal>Here, we only pray at the house or at Dad’s grave.
Have you done your farming for the day?
Oh, good!
It’s almost the weekend.//<portrait=happy>But you already knew that.
I was just thinking about checking up on you!
I’ve always been close to my mom. I wish I could have had a bit more time with Dad, but it’s no use mourning now.
Dad had a happy and long life.//I don’t think it’s fair for me to ask for more. After all, a long and happy life is all anyone wants, right?
There are plenty of flowers around the lake… I had no idea you liked flowers.
I was going to pick some flowers the other day, but I wasn’t sure if I had anybody special to give them to.//<portrait=normal>That’s true… I guess I can always give them to my mom.
The cavern… Let’s talk about that. I think there’s more life in there than people think.//<portrait=surprised>Well, you’ve been inside, right? What do you think?
It’s really fun hanging out with you. Feel free to stop me if I monopolize the conversation too much, okay?
It’s hard for me to get a day off… Since, as you know, it’s just <NpcName>Frank</> and me at the Tavern.//<portrait=happy>But when I do, I’ll come by the farm and check up on you, okay?
I like that you get along with my mom. It really shows what type of person you are…
She’s been asking about us lately…errr, you, I guess. Asking about you in relation to me, to be specific.

Here’s what I’m thinking: if the Tavern stays open longer, and we hire more people, I think both <NpcName>Frank</> and I will get more days off.//<portrait=happy>We’ll also make more money, on top of that.
The tricky part is finding more people to train…and convincing <NpcName>Frank</> to spend more.//<portrait=annoyed>Good luck to me, I guess.
I’ve been watching too much TV lately. I need to get out more.
Usually, when I get headaches like this, it’s because I need a new prescription for my glasses.
Ugh… This can’t be good.
Sometimes I think I should just give up trying to run the Tavern and let <NpcName>Frank</> take over.
But then I remember the Tavern is a legacy.//<portrait=normal>It was my parents’, and someday, <NpcName>Frank</> and I will pass it to the next generation.
Sometimes I wonder what my life would have been like if I’d stayed in Pokyo after university.
But I am who I am. I’ve realized I like familiarity, and the familiarity I like the most is right here.
Do I have cat hair on me?
I played with Peanut and Butter earlier, and there was a lot of hair on my shirt.//I think I got most of it off.
Hey! So nice to run into you, <PlayerName>$player</>.
I was a bit bored… But I feel better now, after talking to you.//<portrait=normal>Thanks for asking.
Can you keep a secret?
There’s something about cats, isn’t there? It makes me feel special when my brother’s cats come to visit me.//<portrait=blushing>They really know how to steal my heart, those furballs.
I enjoyed having a picnic with you that time.//<portrait=normal>If I promise to make you something else besides fried eggs…could we do that again sometime?
No promises, though…about the eggs.//<portrait=happy>The picnic, yes, I promise!
I think at this point in our lives, you and I both know there’s more out there than just us living in this universe.
I never really gave a lot of thought to having my own family.
Maybe when the right person comes along, I can start thinking about it.
The first thing I did after graduating was move back here.
I feel guilty for spending a lot of money on university and never actually using my degree to get one of those fancy jobs at a big firm.
I wonder if I should start learning how to cook fancy things, like lodeh or pumpkin pie.//Well, anything besides fried eggs, really.
Do you like people who can cook? Or no?//<portrait=sad>I can cook a little, by the way. I mean, I’m not too bad at it, if you’re into that sort of stuff. Um…
That…errr…looks good on you…
Oh my! Good. That looks good on you. The shirt.
I don’t know how I would have coped if you hadn’t been there that time when my mom fell.//I was such a wreck.
I’m glad to have someone like you in my life.
Would you like to have a big family, <PlayerName>$player</>?
I think I would like that.

Special.SourceString: Depends. If it’s with you, then yes.

Text.SourceString: I think I get what you’re saying.

Special.SourceString: No. I like me and just me.

Text.SourceString: Yeah, questions like that always catch me off guard. I have no idea why I asked you that.
Do you hang out with anyone special on the weekends?
<NpcName>Alice</> is a childhood friend. We both like talking about mysteries and picking each other’s brains.
There’s nothing going on between <NpcName>Alice</> and me.//We’re just friends. I love her like my own sister.
It’s tough to concentrate with you around… You’re so distracting!
No, no, don’t go. I meant it in a good way. I would rather be here than doing something else.
Your cheeks are getting red. You need to warm up…
I would offer to warm you up, but…I’m afraid you might say no.
I can’t believe they don’t have pineapples.//I specifically came here looking for them.
They ran out of tea leaves.//<portrait=concerned>I guess we won’t be serving green tea at the Tavern tomorrow.
Hmm…
Your farm is just over the creek, right?
We should have picnics here more often.//<portrait=blushing>Just you and me.
I know I tend to complain a lot, but I really don’t mean it.//<portrait=concerned>I was just venting, you know?
Thank you for being such a great listener.//<portrait=happy>And an even better friend.
What do you think?//<portrait=normal>Would I look all right with longer hair, or no?
I’m really looking forward to all the fun things I have planned for this Spring.//Everything’s gonna start to bloom soon!
One of the only good things about Summer is the fact that you can wear colorful shirts, but even that gets old after a while.
Sorry if I’m grumpy… I just can’t stand the heat and the humidity of Summer.
On a lighter note, I love the excuse to be lazy and do nothing all day because it’s too hot to do anything else.

I hope we don’t start getting half-naked customers, being near the beach and all.//<portrait=annoyed>The only place where it’s socially acceptable to wear a bathing suit and flip-flops all day is the beach, never the Tavern.
I hate having to run the heater all the time. It’s so expensive, and it dries out the air at the Tavern.
I’m so glad Spring is here! The weather is finally starting to warm up.
I always feel like a weight has been lifted off my shoulders when Winter ends and Spring begins.//It’s safe for Mom to walk outside again. No more ice.
I’m looking forward to going on long walks with my mom and enjoying the beautiful Fall scenery.
I’m really enjoying the slower pace of life in Fall. It’s a nice change from the busy Summer.//<portrait=happy>The beach is peaceful again. Ha ha!
My brother <NpcName>Frank</> hates durian, but I think he’s out of his mind.//It’s the best fruit ever.

I always try to add durian to the menu and always fail ’cause <NpcName>Frank</> removes it right away. Who made him the boss?//<portrait=normal>Think of all the desserts you can make from it! Oh, sounds so good!
I love the way durian smells. Some people say it smells bad, but I think it smells amazing.
We used to have more mirrors here, but since we took them out for Dad’s funeral, we’ve been kind of too lazy to put them back.
Mom has this thing where we must remove all mirrors during the funeral of a family member.//Bad luck, she said.
